8-bit signed integer will result in undefined behavior.If an arithmetic operation (such as addition or multiplication) attempts to create a value outside the range that can be represented, this is calledinteger overflow(orarithmetic overflow). For signed integers, integer overflow will result in undefined behavior.#include <iostream>

